Data: Collected through a live experiment consisting of 20 trials (10 with the nose pinched, 10 without).

Methodology: Performed a Permutation Test using the infer package in R to simulate the null distribution.

Results: The calculated p-value was 0.29.

Conclusion: Since the p-value is greater than the significance level of 0.05, we fail to reject the null hypothesis. 
There is insufficient evidence to conclude that pinching the nose significantly affects flavor identification in this experiment.
